WEBVTT - Close Eye Founder Story

scene-0-line-0
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.500
Hi.

scene-0-line-1
00:00:00.900 --> 00:00:01.481
I'm Krishna.

scene-0-line-2
00:00:01.881 --> 00:00:02.463
Not the Founder.

scene-0-line-3
00:00:02.863 --> 00:00:03.444
Not the CEO.

scene-0-line-4
00:00:03.844 --> 00:00:04.344
Just Krishna.

scene-1-line-0
00:00:06.344 --> 00:00:08.088
Thank you for taking a few minutes to listen.

scene-1-line-1
00:00:08.488 --> 00:00:09.844
Before I tell you about Close Eye,

scene-1-line-2
00:00:10.244 --> 00:00:12.569
I want to tell you about one day that changed my life.

scene-2-line-0
00:00:14.569 --> 00:00:16.119
A little while ago, on a June morning,

scene-2-line-1
00:00:16.519 --> 00:00:17.294
my daughter was born.

scene-2-line-2
00:00:17.694 --> 00:00:19.244
It was the happiest day of my life —

scene-2-line-3
00:00:19.644 --> 00:00:20.807
and, unexpectedly, one of the loneliest.

scene-3-line-0
00:00:22.807 --> 00:00:24.744
In that room there were only a few of us.

scene-3-line-1
00:00:25.144 --> 00:00:26.113
My wife. Our newborn daughter.

scene-3-line-2
00:00:26.513 --> 00:00:28.257
My sister-in-law, who never left our side.

scene-3-line-3
00:00:28.657 --> 00:00:29.238
And my parents.

scene-3-line-4
00:00:29.638 --> 00:00:30.995
Everyone else I loved was far away.

scene-4-line-0
00:00:32.995 --> 00:00:34.351
There was no crowd outside the door.

scene-4-line-1
00:00:34.751 --> 00:00:35.914
No phone buzzing every few minutes —

scene-4-line-2
00:00:36.314 --> 00:00:38.445
"Is it a boy or a girl?"  "How's the baby?"

scene-4-line-3
00:00:38.845 --> 00:00:40.201
For a few moments, everything went quiet.

scene-5-line-0
00:00:42.201 --> 00:00:43.751
I held my daughter for the first time.

scene-5-line-1
00:00:44.151 --> 00:00:45.895
I wanted to share that joy with the world.

scene-5-line-2
00:00:46.295 --> 00:00:48.233
And I realised I had almost no one to call.

scene-5-line-3
00:00:48.633 --> 00:00:49.795
For the first time, I understood

scene-5-line-4
00:00:50.195 --> 00:00:50.970
what loneliness feels like

scene-5-line-5
00:00:51.370 --> 00:00:52.533
in life's most precious moment.

scene-6-line-0
00:00:54.533 --> 00:00:55.308
Then a thought came —

scene-6-line-1
00:00:55.708 --> 00:00:56.871
the one every parent quietly carries.

scene-6-line-2
00:00:57.271 --> 00:00:58.433
"What if something happens to me?"

scene-6-line-3
00:00:58.833 --> 00:00:59.996
Her mother would always love her.

scene-6-line-4
00:01:00.396 --> 00:01:01.558
Her grandparents would always protect her.

scene-6-line-5
00:01:01.958 --> 00:01:03.315
But I wished there was something more.

scene-7-line-0
00:01:05.315 --> 00:01:06.283
Not someone to replace family.

scene-7-line-1
00:01:06.683 --> 00:01:07.458
Something to strengthen it.

scene-7-line-2
00:01:07.858 --> 00:01:08.440
A trusted circle.

scene-7-line-3
00:01:08.840 --> 00:01:09.421
A trusted presence.

scene-7-line-4
00:01:09.821 --> 00:01:10.984
People who would stand beside her

scene-7-line-5
00:01:11.384 --> 00:01:12.352
if life ever became hard.

scene-8-line-0
00:01:14.352 --> 00:01:15.515
And I realised millions of families

scene-8-line-1
00:01:15.915 --> 00:01:16.884
already live with this feeling.

scene-8-line-2
00:01:17.284 --> 00:01:17.865
Parents growing old.

scene-8-line-3
00:01:18.265 --> 00:01:19.040
Children living oceans away.

scene-8-line-4
00:01:19.440 --> 00:01:20.021
Grandparents missing birthdays.

scene-8-line-5
00:01:20.421 --> 00:01:21.971
Families separated by cities, by countries, by life.

scene-8-line-6
00:01:22.371 --> 00:01:23.146
Every night, someone wonders,

scene-8-line-7
00:01:23.546 --> 00:01:24.128
"Are they okay?"

scene-9-line-0
00:01:26.128 --> 00:01:27.290
That was the moment Close Eye

scene-9-line-1
00:01:27.690 --> 00:01:28.659
stopped being a startup idea.

scene-9-line-2
00:01:29.059 --> 00:01:29.834
It became my responsibility.

scene-9-line-3
00:01:30.234 --> 00:01:31.590
Close Eye exists so that no family

scene-9-line-4
00:01:31.990 --> 00:01:33.347
faces life's most important moments alone.

scene-10-line-0
00:01:35.347 --> 00:01:36.897
We don't replace relationships. We strengthen them.

scene-10-line-1
00:01:37.297 --> 00:01:38.653
We don't replace sons or daughters —

scene-10-line-2
00:01:39.053 --> 00:01:40.603
we help them stay present, even across distance.

scene-10-line-3
00:01:41.003 --> 00:01:41.972
We don't replace parents —

scene-10-line-4
00:01:42.372 --> 00:01:43.728
we help families care for one another

scene-10-line-5
00:01:44.128 --> 00:01:45.097
with dignity, trust, and compassion.

scene-11-line-0
00:01:47.097 --> 00:01:48.066
Every visit. Every WhatsApp update.

scene-11-line-1
00:01:48.466 --> 00:01:49.241
Every companion. Every conversation.

scene-11-line-2
00:01:49.641 --> 00:01:50.610
Is a family trusting us.

scene-11-line-3
00:01:51.010 --> 00:01:51.979
When you join Close Eye,

scene-11-line-4
00:01:52.379 --> 00:01:53.541
you're not joining a startup.

scene-11-line-5
00:01:53.941 --> 00:01:55.297
You're becoming someone's trusted presence.

scene-12-line-0
00:01:57.297 --> 00:01:58.460
I made another promise that day.

scene-12-line-1
00:01:58.860 --> 00:02:00.604
Close Eye should never exist only for its founders.

scene-12-line-2
00:02:01.004 --> 00:02:02.748
It should grow with the people who build it.

scene-12-line-3
00:02:03.148 --> 00:02:03.923
Think like an owner.

scene-12-line-4
00:02:04.323 --> 00:02:04.904
Build with integrity.

scene-12-line-5
00:02:05.304 --> 00:02:05.804
Protect trust.

scene-12-line-6
00:02:06.204 --> 00:02:07.560
Because trust is never built by software.

scene-12-line-7
00:02:07.960 --> 00:02:08.929
Trust is built by people.

scene-13-line-0
00:02:10.929 --> 00:02:12.479
So every year, on the same June day,

scene-13-line-1
00:02:12.879 --> 00:02:14.429
we won't only mark a company anniversary.

scene-13-line-2
00:02:14.829 --> 00:02:15.798
We'll celebrate Family Day —

scene-13-line-3
00:02:16.198 --> 00:02:17.554
a reminder of why Close Eye exists,

scene-13-line-4
00:02:17.954 --> 00:02:19.117
that every request is a family,

scene-13-line-5
00:02:19.517 --> 00:02:21.067
and that no technology replaces genuine human presence.

scene-14-line-0
00:02:23.067 --> 00:02:24.811
One day, I hope you'll meet my daughter.

scene-14-line-1
00:02:25.211 --> 00:02:26.373
Not because she's our brand —

scene-14-line-2
00:02:26.773 --> 00:02:28.324
but because she reminds us why this matters:

scene-14-line-3
00:02:28.724 --> 00:02:29.499
every child deserves grandparents,

scene-14-line-4
00:02:29.899 --> 00:02:31.255
every grandparent deserves a grandchild's laughter,

scene-14-line-5
00:02:31.655 --> 00:02:33.011
and every family deserves to stay close,

scene-14-line-6
00:02:33.411 --> 00:02:34.186
no matter the distance.

scene-15-line-0
00:02:36.186 --> 00:02:37.543
Thank you for believing in this mission.

scene-15-line-1
00:02:37.943 --> 00:02:39.493
Thank you for becoming part of Close Eye.

scene-15-line-2
00:02:39.893 --> 00:02:40.668
Together, let's build

scene-15-line-3
00:02:41.068 --> 00:02:42.424
the world's most trusted presence network.

scene-16-line-0
00:02:44.424 --> 00:02:45.393
Before you enter the dashboard…

scene-16-line-1
00:02:45.793 --> 00:02:47.343
I'd like you to remember one thing.

scene-16-line-2
00:02:47.743 --> 00:02:48.518
Every notification you receive…

scene-16-line-3
00:02:48.918 --> 00:02:49.887
Every phone call you answer…

scene-16-line-4
00:02:50.287 --> 00:02:51.256
Every WhatsApp message you send…

scene-16-line-5
00:02:51.656 --> 00:02:52.431
Every visit you coordinate…

scene-16-line-6
00:02:52.831 --> 00:02:53.606
Every decision you make…

scene-16-line-7
00:02:54.006 --> 00:02:54.974
Will represent someone's family.

scene-16-line-8
00:02:55.374 --> 00:02:57.118
Someone will sleep peacefully tonight because of your work.

scene-16-line-9
00:02:57.518 --> 00:02:58.293
That is our responsibility.

scene-16-line-10
00:02:58.693 --> 00:02:59.468
That is our privilege.

scene-16-line-11
00:02:59.868 --> 00:03:01.225
And that is why Close Eye exists.

scene-16-line-12
00:03:01.625 --> 00:03:02.787
Close Eye doesn't replace relationships.

scene-16-line-13
00:03:03.187 --> 00:03:03.768
It protects them.

scene-16-line-14
00:03:04.168 --> 00:03:04.750
It strengthens them.

scene-16-line-15
00:03:05.150 --> 00:03:06.506
It helps them grow, even across distance.

scene-16-line-16
00:03:06.906 --> 00:03:07.681
Welcome to Close Eye.

scene-16-line-17
00:03:08.081 --> 00:03:09.631
Thank you for becoming someone's Trusted Presence.
